You’re right to double‑check that. In your snippet, baseline is only null when isCreate == true. You only call processChanges(...) when !isCreate, so baseline is guaranteed non‑null there. Safe. 👍

Here’s a clean wrapper so you don’t pass a bare ObjectNode.

1) Result wrapper

package com.neo.notification.snapshot;

import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.node.ObjectNode;

public final class SnapshotResult {
    public enum Source { LATEST, BASELINE, NONE }

    private final Source source;
    private final ObjectNode json;

    private SnapshotResult(Source source, ObjectNode json) {
        this.source = source;
        this.json = json;
    }

    public static SnapshotResult latest(ObjectNode json)   { return new SnapshotResult(Source.LATEST, json); }
    public static SnapshotResult baseline(ObjectNode json) { return new SnapshotResult(Source.BASELINE, json); }
    public static SnapshotResult none()                    { return new SnapshotResult(Source.NONE, null); }

    public Source source()      { return source; }
    public ObjectNode json()    { return json; }
    public boolean isCreate()   { return source == Source.NONE; }
}

2) Reader that returns the wrapper

package com.neo.notification.snapshot;

import com.azure.storage.blob.*;
import com.azure.storage.blob.models.PagedIterable;
import com.azure.storage.blob.models.TaggedBlobItem;
import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.node.ObjectNode;

import java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;
import java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;
import java.util.logging.Logger;

public final class GetSnapshotFromBlob {
    private static final com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper MAPPER =
            new com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper();

    public static SnapshotResult getSnapshotFromBlobStorage(
            BlobContainerClient dataContainer,
            String logicalContainer,
            String docId,
            Logger log) throws java.io.IOException {

        // 1) Try the latest via index tags
        String query = String.format("logicalContainer = '%s' AND docId = '%s' AND isLatest = 'true'",
                                     logicalContainer, docId);
        PagedIterable<TaggedBlobItem> blobItems = dataContainer.findBlobsByTags(query);
        TaggedBlobItem item = blobItems.stream().findFirst().orElse(null);
        if (item != null) {
            BlobClient latest = dataContainer.getBlobClient(item.getName());
            ObjectNode json = readJsonObject(latest, log);
            log.info("Snapshot source=LATEST: " + item.getName());
            return SnapshotResult.latest(json);
        }

        // 2) Fallback to baseline {container}/{docId}/{docId}.json
        String baselinePath = logicalContainer + "/" + docId + "/" + docId + ".json";
        BlobClient baseline = dataContainer.getBlobClient(baselinePath);
        if (baseline.exists()) {
            ObjectNode json = readJsonObject(baseline, log);
            log.info("Snapshot source=BASELINE: " + baselinePath);
            return SnapshotResult.baseline(json);
        }

        // 3) Truly first time (create)
        log.info("Snapshot source=NONE (create) for id=" + docId);
        return SnapshotResult.none();
    }

    private static ObjectNode readJsonObject(BlobClient client, Logger log) throws java.io.IOException {
        try (ByteArrayOutputStream out = new ByteArrayOutputStream()) {
            client.download(out);
            String json = out.toString(StandardCharsets.UTF_8);
            return (ObjectNode) MAPPER.readTree(json);
        } catch (Exception e) {
            log.severe("Failed to read blob '" + client.getBlobName() + "': " + e.getMessage());
            // Propagate so the caller can decide to retry/abort
            if (e instanceof java.io.IOException) throw (java.io.IOException) e;
            throw new java.io.IOException(e);
        }
    }
}

3) Using it in your Function

final String docId = newDoc.get("id").asText();

SnapshotResult snap;
try {
    snap = GetSnapshotFromBlob.getSnapshotFromBlobStorage(DATA_CONTAINER, cosmosContainerName, docId, context.getLogger());
} catch (IOException io) {
    // Storage hiccup; let Functions retry
    throw new RuntimeException(io);
}

boolean isCreate = snap.isCreate();
ObjectNode baseline = snap.json(); // non-null when !isCreate

List<ChangeInfo> deltas = List.of();
if (!isCreate) {
    deltas = TrackedChangeHandler.processChanges(
        cosmosContainerName, newDoc, DATA_CONTAINER, fieldsToTrack, baseline, context.getLogger());
    if (deltas.isEmpty()) {
        context.getLogger().info("No tracked changes for id=" + docId);
        continue;
    }
}

// Build and send message (eventType tells downstream CREATE vs MODIFY)
String eventType = isCreate ? "CREATE" : "MODIFY";
ServiceBusMessage msg = MessageFactory.build(newDoc, baseline, eventType, cosmosContainerName);
busSender.sendMessage(msg);

// After successful send, persist snapshot/version as needed…

This keeps the logic clear:
	•	Wrapper tells you where the snapshot came from.
	•	isCreate() is a one-liner decision.
	•	baseline is only used when !isCreate, so it won’t be null in the delta computation.